Several people alleged to be involved in the disappearance of a Tongaat teen are due back in court today. He was last seen by witnesses who say he was beaten at a popular lounge after being accused of alcohol theft. Courtesy #DStv403 TONGAAT - Seven suspects accused of kidnapping and murdering a Tongaat teenager in KwaZulu-Natal are expected back in court on Tuesday to apply for bail. One of the accused -- a 16-year-old minor -- told the court last week that he will no longer apply for bail. READ: Probe into Tongaat cops' conduct All are facing charges of kidnapping and murder of Andile "Bobo" Mbuthu. It's alleged that Mbuthu went missing after allegedly stealing alcohol from a local tavern. His decomposed remains were found by police divers in a river near his home.